Subject: Re: [T2] New cd player cuts out [fixed now!]

Thanks to ideas from George Lyle, my cd player can now withstand voltage
dips caused by turn signals, brake lights, even the rear-window defroster --
even all at once. Total cost: about $4.00.
This might be helpful to others who said they had the same problem:
(I hope it all lines up properly)



switched power ------------&------------ cd player (& = splice)
                                            |
                                            |
                                       diode (Radio Shack part number
                                            |     276-1144; $1.49 for two)
                                            |
                                   [+side of capacitor]
                              electrolytic capacitor (#272-1047; $2.49)
                                        [-side]
                                            |
                                            |
                                         Ground

Works great and all the wires are hidden.

Thanks, George.

John
